¬¬Microsoft's seamlessly connected Microsoft Dynamics CRM and Microsoft Outlook solution provides the power of a 360 degree view of the customer, with an easy to use and familiar interface.  Staff can continue to use the Outlook email client to access CRM data and so are more confident, get things done faster and don't have to learn to use a new application.

Microsoft Dynamics’ automated workflow capability allows you to replace manual processes with automation, generating documentation and prompting staff and management when their involvement is needed. So they have more time to focus on their role.
Microsoft SharePoint enables your staff to store and collaborate on documents securely, taking care of version control, access permissions and it is available on any device.

Transform the way people work by adopting a connected, more collaborative approach to meeting and getting things done.  The Microsoft Lync platform enables staff to have online meetings ‘on-the-fly’, share screens and collaborate, video call and send instant messages.  Teams are more agile, can pick the right communication channel based on presence information and respond faster to pressing challenges with easier access to people.

Windows powered tablets and mobile devices allow staff to access documents and store notes wherever they, negating the need to travel back to a desk to record outcomes and pick up tasks. Travel costs are reduced and admin time is reduced, increasing productivity.
Roll over / tap the bullet points for more information.

Through effective content delivery, collaboration, unified communications and mobility solutions, Microsoft technologies enable professional services companies to streamline the management and control of content, data, and processes across the business.  A consistent productivity experience helps simplify how people work together, sell more effectively, and meet customer needs more consistently.
